Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20iconic%2023-ounce%20cans%20of%20Arizona%20Iced%20Tea%20still%20sell%20for%2099%20cents%20after%2032%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EArizona%20founder%20Don%20Vultaggio%20told%20Today%20he%20doesn't%20want%20to%20raise%20prices%20on%20consumers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20strategy%20is%20unique%20as%20grocery%20prices%20rise%20and%20some%20brands%20use%20shrinkflation%20to%20profit%20more.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDon%20Vultaggio%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20company%20behind%20Arizona%20Iced%20Tea%2C%20still%20sells%20his%20product%20for%20the%20same%20price%20as%20when%20it%20launched%2032%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%94%2099%20cents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVultaggio%20decided%20to%20get%20into%20tea%20and%20founded%20the%20Arizona%20beverage%20company%20in%20New%20York%20in%201992%20after%20seeing%20the%20success%20of%20Snapple.%20Arizona's%20signature%20big%20cans%20of%20iced%20tea%20were%20a%20quick%20success%2C%20and%20Vultaggio%20still%20runs%20the%20company%20to%20this%20day%20with%20the%20help%20of%20his%20sons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-youre-still-spending-much-of-your-budget-on-food-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egroceries%20have%20gotten%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20some%20brands%20engage%20in%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrinkflation-grocery-stores-pringles-cereal-candy-bars-chocolate-toilet-paper-cadbury-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshrinkflation%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20keeping%20their%20price%20the%20same%20while%20decreasing%20the%20amount%20of%20product%20in%20a%20package%20%E2%80%94%20Arizona%20has%20managed%20to%20offer%20its%20iconic%2023-ounce%20cans%20for%20the%20same%20price%20it%20always%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.today.com%2Fvideo%2Flearn-the-sweet-success-story-behind-arizona-s-i