ut%20the%20year%2C%20and%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20to%20get%20an%20email%20from%20the%20administration%20warning%20that%20some%20kids%20are%20coming%20home%20with%20rashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20rashes%20I%20had%20seen%20on%20my%20kids%20were%20minor%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskin-bumps-that-look-like-pimples-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elittle%20bumps%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20fingers%20or%20the%20back%20of%20their%20hands.%20Nothing%20like%20mine%2C%20which%20spread%20on%20my%20arms%2C%20chest%2C%20back%2C%20legs%2C%20and%20toes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20caterpillars'%20hairs%20contain%20a%20toxin%20that%2C%20when%20brushed%20against%20skin%2C%20produces%20a%20poison%20ivy-like%20rash%20that%20is%20incredibly%20itchy%20and%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDerek%20V.%20Chan%2C%20a%20board-certified%20%3Cspan%3Emedical%20and%20cosmetic%20dermatologist%3C%2Fspan%3E%20at%20All%20Dermis%20Dermatology%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20said%20it's%20key%20not%20to%20scratch%20the%20initial%20bumps.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20spread%20the%20toxin%20and%20hairs%20to%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20body%20and%20cause%20new%20lesions%20to%20develop%20elsewhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Chan%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2283895456-21a9-4575-a81a-d18f8bc662aa%5C%22%3EI%20tried%20over-the-counter%20products%2C%20but%20nothing%20worked%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20my%20dermatologist%20prescribed%20a%20topical%20steroid%20medication%2C%20I%20tried%20over-the-counter%20products%20to%20help%20with%20the%20itching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20Benadryl%20before%20bed%20and%20Claritin%20during%20the%20day.%20The%20ointment%20and%20gel%20helped%20ease%20the%20itchiness%2C%20but%20only%20for%20a%20little%20bit.%20I%20was%20especially%20uncomfortable%20at%20night%20and%20would%20wake%20up%20scratching%20my%20skin%20raw.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20trying%20steroid%20cream%2C%20but%20my%20dermatologist%20warned%20me%20that%20I%20wouldn't%20see%20results%20immediately.%20The%20duration%20of%20the%20reaction%20depends%20on%20your%20sensitivity%20to%20the%20toxin.%20In%20some%20people%2C%20it%20can%20last%20several%20weeks%2C%20Chan%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20said%20that%20on%20top%20of%20over-the-counter%20medication%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20cool%20bath%20with%20baking%20soda%20and%2For%20finely%20ground%20colloidal%20oat%20powder%26quot%3B%20can%20ease%20the%20discomfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20already%20picked%20at%20the%20bumps%20%E2%80%94%20like%20I%20did%2C%20because%20I%20couldn't%20stop%20scratching%20%E2%80%94%20Chan%20recommends%20wearing%20sun-protective%20clothing%20to%20avoid%20the%20areas%20getting%20darker%20from%20hyperpigmentation%20and%20always%20wearing%20SPF%20when%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20added%20that%20if%20your%20tongue%20swells%20or%20you%20have%20difficulty%20breathing%20after%20coming%20in%20contact%20with%20the%20toxins%2C%20it%20becomes%20a%20911%20emergency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2248fe8bcb-52bc-4a0a-b933-0ad4e8e5c4b0%5C%22%3EI%20didn't%20touch%20an%20actual%20caterpillar%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20tricky%20about%20browntail%20moth%20is%20that%20you%20don't%20necessarily%20need%20to%20come%20in%20contact%20with%20it%20to%20get%20the%20rash.%20Touching%20an%20item%20that%20the%20moth%20walked%20over%20is%20enough%20to%20generate%20a%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20don't%20know%20where%20I%20came%20in%20contact%20with%20one%20since%20my%20husband%20and%20three%20kids%20were%20thankfully%20spared%20from%20this%20torture.%20The%20only%20thing%20I%20can%20think%20of%20is%20that%20I%20took%20a%20nap%20with%20our%20dogs%20while%20my%20husband%20was%20doing%20bedtime%20with%20the%20kids.%20I%20assume%20they%20rolled%20on%20a%20caterpillar%20or%20a%20nest%20and%20then%20laid%20on%20me%2C%20transferring%20the%20toxins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dermatologist%20said%20she's%20been%20seeing%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20patients%20with%20browntail%20moth%20rashes.%20If%20you're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fregards-portland-maine-everyone-should-be-going-to-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20to%20Maine%20this%20summer%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20your%20kids%20attend%20summer%20camp%20here%2C%20watch%20out%20for%20these%20caterpillars.%20The%20Maine%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20Conservation%20and%20Forestry%20recommends%20using%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maine.gov%2Fdacf%2Fmfs%2Fforest_health%2Finvasive_threats%2Fbrowntail_moth_faqs.htm%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAdults%2520emerge%2520in%2520July%2520and%2C10%2520pm%2520and%252012%2520am.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epesticides%20to%20control%20the%20population%3C%2Fa%3E%20outdoors%20and%20a%20wet%20vac%20to%20remove%20any%20caterpillars%20from%20indoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20added%20that%20after%20spending%20time%20outdoors%2C%20people%20living%20in%20browntail%20moth-prone%20areas%20should%20keep%20their%20skin%20covered%2C%20take%20a%20cool%20shower%20once%20they%20are%20inside%2C%20wash%20clothes%20immediately%20after%2C%20and%20if%20they%20come%20in%20contact%20with%20any%20other%20surface%20where%20hairs%20or%20toxins%20may%20linger%2C%20wash%20bedding%20and%20towels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrowntail-moths-painful-itchy-rash-maine-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719430217000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6675df7d50b021b5cae88677%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrowntail-moths-painful-itchy-rash-maine-2024-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22I%20live%20in%20Maine%20where%20Browntail%20moths%20are%20prevalent.%20I%20woke%20up%20one%20morning%20covered%20head%20to%20toe%20with%20an%20itchy%20and%20painful%20rash.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpreti%40insider.com%20(Conz%20Preti)%22%2C%22en