nder%20Article%2019(1)%20(a)%20and%20Article%2025%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judges%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20pursuing%20an%20undergraduate%20degree%20in%20Computer%20Science%20for%20the%20past%20two%20years%20termed%20the%20CTES%20management's%20decision%20%E2%80%9Carbitrary%2C%20unreasonable%2C%20bad%20in%20law%20and%20perverse%E2%80%9D%20in%20their%20petition%2C%20and%20are%20likely%20to%20challenge%20the%20High%20Court%20verdict%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20through%20their%20lawyer%20Altaf%20Khan%20contended%20that%20the%20new%20dress%20code%20imposed%20by%20the%20college%20violated%20their%20fundamental%20rights%20to%20privacy%2C%20dignity%2C%20and%20religious%20freedom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Khan%20said%20he%20would%20consult%20the%20students%20and%20their%20parents%20before%20moving%20the%20top%20court%20against%20the%20High%20Court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20approaching%20the%20High%20Court%2C%20the%20girls%20had%20also%20written%20to%20the%20University%20of%20Mumbai%2C%20the%20University%20Grants%20Commission%2C%20the%20Vice-Chancellor%2C%20and%20the%20Chancellor%20seeking%20their%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Advocate%20Anil%20Anturkar%20representing%20the%20college%20argued%20that%20the%20dress%20code%20was%20not%20targeted%20at%20only%20Muslims%20but%20was%20uniformly%20applicable%20to%20all%20religious%20symbols.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20college%20policy%20is%20to%20prevent%20the%20open%20display%20of%20religious%20symbols%20unless%20they%20are%20essential%20under%20the%20fundamental%20right%20to%20religion%20such%20as%20the%20turban%20for%20the%20Sikhs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Anturkar%20also%20challenged%20Mr%20Khan%20to%20prove%20his%20contentions%20that%20wearing%20a%20hijab%20is%20an%20essential%20religious%20practice%20in%20Islam%20and%20said%20the%20students%20should%20concentrate%20on%20their%20stu