E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%227%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ERespect%20a%20child%3F%20Shouldn%E2%80%99t%20the%20child%20respect%20the%20adult%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It%20is%20a%20huge%20mindset%20alteration%20in%20our%20adult-centric%20societies%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20respect%20is%20a%20two-way%20street.%20Parents%20observe%20that%20when%20they%20respect%20their%20children%2C%20listen%20to%20their%20opinions%20and%20work%20collaboratively%20with%20them%2C%20they%20automatically%20get%20more%20cooperation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EDemocracy%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20for%20the%20nation%3B%20it%20works%20in%20families%20too.%20Giving%20children%20choices%2C%20trusting%20and%20respecting%20them%20builds%20responsible%20people%20and%20citizens%20down%20the%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%228%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CI%20never%20knew%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20jobs%20of%20a%20parent%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20my%20child%20feels%20loved%20and%20secure.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIn%20this%20fast-paced%20world%2C%20parents%20are%20so%20busy%20making%20sure%20that%20their%20child%20goes%20to%20the%20right%20school%2C%20eats%20the%20right%20food%2C%20and%20goes%20to%20the%20right%20activities%20that%20the%20fundamental%20needs%20of%20the%20child%20are%20lost.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFeeling%20loved%2C%20valued%20and%20safe%20are%20the%20most%20fundamental%20needs%20of%20the%20growing%20child%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20information%20from%20neuroscience.%20Without%20these%20basics%2C%20learning%20cannot%20take%20place.%20The%20question%2C%20%E2%80%9CDoes%20your%20child%20feel%20loved%3F%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20powerful%20wake-up%20call%20for%20parents.%20Learning%20how%20to%20express%20love%20often%20has%20to%20be%20taught%20as%20it%20may%20not%20come%20naturally%20for%20everyone%2C%20or%20they%20may%20have%20never%20experienced%20receiving%20love%20themselves.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%229%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CA%20parent%E2%80%99s%20job%20is%20not%20to%20shame%20or%20punish%20but%20to%20set%20limits%20with%20kindness.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShaming%20and%20yelling%20harm%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20mental%20well-being%20and%20development.%20Parents%20often%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20any%20other%20way.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20these%20sessions%20they%20have%20moved%20from%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CTurn%20off%20that%20video%20game%20right%20now%2C%20you%20useless%20fellow.%20You%20never%20listen%2C%E2%80%9D%20to%20setting%20limits%20with%20sensitivity.%20They%20now%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20know%20you%E2%80%99re%20enjoying%20that%20game%20but%20your%20time%20is%20up%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20sorry%20I%20need%20to%20switch%20this%20off%20for%20you%20as%20you%20are%20finding%20it%20hard%20to%20stop.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20takes%20a%20while%20to%20learn%20these%20skills%20but%20when%20they%20do%2C%20the%20parents%20feel%20like%20they%E2%80%99ve%20found%20a%20key%20to%20a%20new%20world.%20More%20importantly%2C%20parents%20become%20aware%20that%20the%20shift%20has%20led%20to%20their%20children%20feeling%20emotionally%20safe%20with%20them%20and%20having%20better%20self-esteem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20me%20who%20needs%20to%20change%2C%20not%20my%20child%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%93%20At%20the%20end%20of%20our%20parenting%20courses%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20common%20observation%20parents%20make.%20The%20realisation%20that%20stands%20out%20the%20most%20is%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20fixing%20the%20child%20but%20about%20working%20on%20yourself%20which%20then%20brings%20out%20the%20best%20in%20your%20child.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3